# Testing Patterns

Codebase-specific patterns required in tests. These are not optional — missing them causes silent state leaks or CI failures.

## Rollbar Mock (required in any test touching @CronJobExecution)

Every test file that tests a command decorated with `@CronJobExecution` **must** mock rollbar at the top of the file:

```typescript
jest.mock('@config/rollbar.config', () => ({
  rollbar: {
    debug: jest.fn(),
    error: jest.fn(),
    warning: jest.fn(),
    info: jest.fn(),
    wait: jest.fn((cb: () => void) => { cb(); }),
  },
}));
```

Without this mock, the test will attempt to connect to Rollbar and either fail or pollute other tests.

## process.exit Spy Pattern

Commands call `process.exit(0/1)` on completion/error. Always spy and restore:

```typescript
let processExitSpy: jest.SpyInstance;

beforeEach(() => {
  processExitSpy = jest.spyOn(process, 'exit').mockImplementation(() => undefined as never);
});

afterEach(() => {
  processExitSpy.mockRestore(); // use mockRestore, NOT mockReset — removes the spy entirely
});
```

Use `mockRestore()` not `mockReset()` — `mockReset` only clears calls/results but leaves the mock in place, which leaks into other test files.

## Fake Timers (for timeout/setTimeout tests)

Use fake timers when testing shutdown timeouts or any `setTimeout`-dependent logic:

```typescript
beforeEach(() => {
  jest.useFakeTimers();
});

afterEach(() => {
  jest.useRealTimers(); // always restore — fake timers leak between files
});

// Advance time in tests
jest.advanceTimersByTime(30000);
```

## Private Method Testing

Access private methods via type casting when testing internal behavior directly:

```typescript
// Calling a private method
await (command as unknown as {
  handleShutdown: (params: { signal: string }) => Promise<void>;
}).handleShutdown({ signal: 'SIGTERM' });

// Reading/writing private fields
(command as unknown as { isShuttingDown: boolean }).isShuttingDown = true;
(command as unknown as { currentOperation: Promise<void> | null }).currentOperation = Promise.resolve();
```

Spy on private methods using the same cast:

```typescript
const handleShutdownSpy = jest.spyOn(
  command as unknown as { handleShutdown: (params: { signal: string }) => Promise<void> },
  'handleShutdown',
);
handleShutdownSpy.mockResolvedValue(undefined);
// ...
handleShutdownSpy.mockRestore();
```

## Logger Spying

Suppress logger noise and assert log calls:

```typescript
let loggerErrorSpy: jest.SpyInstance;
let loggerDebugSpy: jest.SpyInstance;
let loggerWarnSpy: jest.SpyInstance;

beforeEach(() => {
  loggerErrorSpy = jest.spyOn(Logger.prototype, 'error').mockImplementation(() => undefined);
  loggerDebugSpy = jest.spyOn(Logger.prototype, 'debug').mockImplementation(() => undefined);
  loggerWarnSpy = jest.spyOn(Logger.prototype, 'warn').mockImplementation(() => undefined);
});

afterEach(() => {
  jest.clearAllMocks();
});
```

## Signal Testing

Test signal handlers by emitting directly on `process`:

```typescript
process.emit('SIGHUP', 'SIGHUP');
process.emit('uncaughtException', new Error('test uncaught'));
process.emit('unhandledRejection', 'test rejection', Promise.resolve());
```

Always spy on `handleShutdown` before emitting signals to avoid actually triggering shutdown logic in tests.

## afterEach Discipline

Every test file must have:

```typescript
afterEach(() => {
  jest.clearAllMocks();
});
```

If fake timers or process.exit spy are used, restore them in `afterEach` as well (not `afterAll`).

## Knex Mocking Pattern

For model tests, mock Knex as a chainable query builder:

```typescript
const mockKnexChain = {
  where: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),
  whereNull: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),
  whereIn: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),
  first: jest.fn(),
  select: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),
  insert: jest.fn(),
  update: jest.fn(),
  delete: jest.fn(),
  limit: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),
  offset: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),
  orderBy: jest.fn().mockReturnThis(),
};

const mockKnexRead = jest.fn().mockReturnValue(mockKnexChain);
const mockKnexWrite = jest.fn().mockReturnValue(mockKnexChain);

// In providers:
{ provide: KNEX_READ_CONNECTION, useValue: mockKnexRead },
{ provide: KNEX_WRITE_CONNECTION, useValue: mockKnexWrite },
```

